      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MARKET SNITZ (6) is on debut today for the Simon Miller yard with Pike in the saddle from a favourable draw. His trial coming into this was solid when ducking up the fence and he should get every chance from the barrier today. Finds a suitable race to get off the mark on debut. AUSSIE REACTOR (4) will be fitter for a recent trial behind MARKET SNITZ coming into this event. When first-up last campaign, he flew home to just miss in a stronger race at Ascot and bumped into a few smart ones throughout. Has shown glimpses of talent and he can put it all together now. GLORANARDO (3) ended last campaign with a 4.3L defeat at Bunbury with the form out of that maiden working out well. He won his trial coming into this and if he can return somewhere near his best, he'll be right in the finish. YOUANMI (5) hit the line with MARKET SNITZ in his trial coming in and can't be left out. GETS THE GIRLS (1) is racing well and won't be far away.",
